readme:
Service Usage

OS001 is an Orchestration Service that provides the ability to search and retrieve Biographic and Biometric data associated with a client's Citizenship application.
The search is conducted using a Citizenship Certificate Number, with further filtering by Biographic Criteria (Date of Birth, Family Name and Given Name).

The service orchestrates calls to services 'SV341' and 'IN009' to retrieve biographic data associated with the matching party's business dealing, and to ISR via SV150 to retrieve an associated image.

Service Behaviour

The service will attempt to retrieve data for a single party based on the supplied criteria, according to the following flow and business rules:
Citizenship
OS001.1 The Citizenship Certificate Number ('CCN') is applied to find matching candidate parties:
Matching rules:

  • 'CCN' = PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFER.IDENTIFIERVALUE where IDENTIFIERCODE_TYPE = 'CID'
    OR
  • 'CCN' = DOCUMENT.DOCUMENTNUMBER where DOCUMENT.DOCUMENTTYPE in ('certificateofevidenceofcitizenship', 'citizenship_certificate')

OS001.2 If no parties match 'CCN', a response is returned with the message PRTY00091.
OS001.3 If one or more parties match 'CCN', the Biographic criteria is matched against the ICSE Principal Preferred name of the candidate(s):
Matching rules:

For PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE = 'CID' AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGE_TYPE = '1'

  • 'Date of Birth Year' = BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEYEAR
  • 'Date of Birth Month' = BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEMONTH (if 'Date of Birth Month' not provided match BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEMONTH in (0,-1))
  • 'Date of Birth Day' = BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEDAY (if 'Date of Birth Day' not provided match BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEDAY in (0,-1))
  • 'Family Name' = BIOGRAPHIC.FAMILY_NAME
  • 'Given Name' = BIOGRAPHIC.GIVENNAME (If 'Given Name' not provided match BIOGRAPHIC.GIVENNAME = '')

OS001.4 If no parties match (CCN + Biographic criteria), a response is returned with the message PRTY00092.
OS001.5 If multiple parties match (CCN + Biographic criteria), a response is returned with the message PRTY00093.
OS001.6 Where a single party is matched after applying (CCN + Biographic criteria), a response will be sent as follows:
Response: Biographic Data
OS001.7 If IncludeBiographicFlag = 'T', Biographic Data will be returned as follows:
Return Biographic details where PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGE_TYPE = '1'
Set NameUsageType = 'Principal Preferred'.

OS001.7.1 If AliasNameFlag = 'T'
Also return Biographic details where
PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE = '2' OR PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE not in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE in ('1', '2')

Set NameUsageType = 'Alias' for all names returned as a result of AliasNameFlag = 'T'.

OS001.7.2 If AliasExistsFlag = 'T'
Also return AliasExistsFlag.
Set = 'T' where exists (
PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE = '2' OR PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE not in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE in ('1', '2')
)
Else Set 'F'

Response: Other Data
OS001.8 Deceased Indicator:
Set 'T' where exists DEATH.EFFECTIVETOTIMESTAMP IS NULL.
ELSE Set 'F'

OS001.9 Citizenship Status:
If exists CITIZENSHIP where BUSINESSSERVICEROLE.ROLESTATUS = '5' SET = 'Acquired' ElseIf exists CITIZENSHIP where BUSINESSSERVICEROLE.ROLESTATUS = '9' SET = 'Loss'
ElseIf exists CITIZENSHIP where BUSINESSSERVICEROLE.ROLE_STATUS = '3' SET = 'Approved not Acquired'
Else SET = 'Not Approved'.

OS001.10 Document Status:
For CCN that matched:
If exists DOCUMENTEVENT.DOCUMENTEVENTTYPE = 'VOIDEDREASON' SET = 'Void'.
Else SET = 'Current'

Response: Image
If IncludeImage = 'T' the OS service will attempt to retrieve the latest Citizenship Image from ISR via SV150, where it is lawful to disclose:
Retrieve Rules:
Call SV150 with the image id of the latest (based on localfacialacquisitiontimestamp) BIOMETRICENROLMENT where
BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSCONTEXTTEXT = 'Citizenship' and BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSEVENTTEXT IN ('Citizenshipinterview','CitizenshipTest')
And localfacialacquisitiontimestamp) >= '2009-09-17' And BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCE. BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCETYPE = 'FC'
If no such image id exists
Call SV150 with the image id of the latest (based on localfacialacquisitiontimestamp) BIOMETRICENROLMENT where
BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSCONTEXTTEXT= 'Citizenship' and BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSEVENTTEXT NOT IN ('Citizenshipinterview','CitizenshipTest')
And BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCE. BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCE_TYPE = 'FC'

OS001.11 If no Image exists. Return message PRTY00095
OS001.12 If Image exists but not lawful to return. Return message PRTY00096.
OS001.13 If Image exists but ISR cannot find image. Return message PRTY00097
OS001.14 If Image Retrieve is successful, return message PRTY00094.
OS001.15 If IncludeImage = 'F', return message PRTY00094.
OS001.16 IsImageAvailable (FaciaImageCount):
If image exists set = 'T' Else 'F'
